10px;">
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Programming note: </strong><em>Money S=
tuff is going to be off for a few weeks starting tomorrow. I planned this b=
efore Elon Musk tried to cancel his Twitter deal, and I am not a monster, s=
o there will be occasional columns as Musk or other news require. But it wi=
ll not publish every day; we=E2=80=99ll resume normal service sometime in A=
ugust.</em></p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Cake</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Not much is going on today, so=C2=A0I thought =
we might talk about=C2=A0an interesting <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/28351521.280590/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucG90dGVyYW5kZXJzb24uY=
29tL21lZGlhL2V4cGVyaWVuY2UvOTQyXzIwMjEuMDQuMzAlMjAtJTIwTWVtLiUyME9wbi4lMjAt=
JTIwU25vdyUyMFBoaXBwcyUyMEdyb3VwJTIwdi4lMjBLQ2FrZSUyMEFjcXVpc2l0aW9uJTIwLSU=
yME1jQ29ybWljay5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe13b10e0/email" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000=
; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom=
-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Delaw=
are Chancery Court decision</a>=C2=A0from last April. In March 2020, a priv=
ate equity fund, Kohlberg &amp; Co.,=C2=A0signed a merger agreement to buy =
a company called DecoPac Holdings Inc., which =E2=80=9Csells cake decoratio=
ns and technology to supermarkets for use in their in-store bakeries,=E2=80=
=9D in a=C2=A0$550 million leveraged buyout. Kohlberg also got commitment l=
etters from lenders to provide debt financing for the deal.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Then=C2=A0the Covid-19 pandemic got worse,=C2=
=A0the supermarket-cake-decorating business declined, and Kohlberg =E2=80=
=9Clost their appetite for the deal shortly after signing it.=E2=80=9D So, =
as the judge =E2=80=94 then-Vice Chancellor=C2=A0Kathaleen McCormick =E2=80=
=94 writes, =E2=80=9Cthe buyers called their litigation counsel and began e=
valuating ways to get out of the deal.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">They came up with three approaches:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">They said that DecoPac had experience=
d a =E2=80=9Cmaterial adverse effect=E2=80=9D due to the decline in its bus=
iness during the pandemic. If there was an MAE, then Kohlberg could termina=
te the agreement.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">They said that D=
ecoPac had not complied with its covenant to =E2=80=9Coperate the Business =
in the Ordinary Course of Business,=E2=80=9D because it had done unusual=C2=
=A0things (like draw on a revolver) to respond to the pandemic. If DecoPac =
breached its covenants, then Kohlberg could terminate.</li>=09<li style=3D"=
margin-bottom: 5px;">They took steps to blow up their financing, sending ex=
aggeratedly bad projections to their lenders along =E2=80=9Cwith demands fo=
r more favorable debt financing terms.=E2=80=9D Asked for better financing =
for a worse deal, the lenders declined, and Kohlberg did not get its financ=
ing. This is important because the contract allowed DecoPac to seek specifi=
c performance, that is, ask a Delaware court to order Kohlberg to pay the $=
550 million and close the deal, but only if =E2=80=9Cfull proceeds of the D=
ebt Financing have been funded to Buyer.=E2=80=9D By blowing up the debt fi=
nancing, Kohlberg planned to avoid specific performance: Even if the court =
didn=E2=80=99t believe it about the MAE or covenant stuff, it wouldn=E2=80=
=99t order Kohlberg to close the deal if the debt financing wasn=E2=80=99t =
available.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So Kohlberg canceled the deal and DecoPac sued=
. The vice chancellor was not amused by Kohlberg=E2=80=99s excuses:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At trial, the plaintiffs proved that DecoPac d=
id not breach the MAE representation, given the durational insignificance a=
nd corresponding immateriality of the decline in sales. They also proved th=
at, even if it was reasonable to expect that these sales declines would giv=
e rise to an MAE, the seller-friendly exception for events =E2=80=9Crelated=
 to=E2=80=9D government orders applied, and DecoPac had not suffered dispro=
portionately to comparable companies. The=C2=A0plaintiffs likewise demonstr=
ated that DecoPac operated in the ordinary course of business in all materi=
al respects. The plaintiffs further proved that the buyers breached their o=
bligation to use reasonable best efforts in connection with the debt financ=
ing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Adding another layer of complication to the an=
alysis, the buyers claim that, despite these holdings, it need not close. T=
hey rely on a contractual exception to the parties=E2=80=99 agreement condi=
tioning the seller=E2=80=99s right to specific performance on fully funded =
debt financing. Because there is no debt financing in place, the buyers arg=
ue that the court may not grant specific performance. The court disagrees. =
Applying the prevention doctrine, this decision deems the debt financing co=
ndition met because the buyers contributed materially to lack of debt finan=
cing by breaching their reasonable-best-efforts obligation.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Chalking up a victory for deal certainty, this=
 post-trial decision resolves all issues in favor of the seller and orders =
the buyers to close on the purchase agreement.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On specific performance in particular, she wro=
te:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CA party seeking specific performance =
must establish that (1) a valid contract exists, (2) he is ready, willing, =
and able to perform, and (3) that the balance of equities tips in favor of =
the party seeking performance.=E2=80=9D This court has not hesitated to ord=
er specific=C2=A0performance in cases of this nature, particularly where so=
phisticated parties represented by sophisticated counsel stipulate that spe=
cific performance would be an appropriate remedy in the event of breach.</p=
>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here, the parties stipulated to the remedy of =
specific performance, but that stipulation applies =E2=80=9C<em>if and only=
 if</em> . . . the full proceeds of the Debt Financing have been funded to =
Buyer on the terms set forth in the [DCL] to fund the payment of the Estima=
ted=C2=A0Closing Payment at Closing (or would be funded at the Closing if t=
he equity Financing is substantially contemporaneously funded at the Closin=
g)=E2=80=9D (the =E2=80=9Cdebt-funding condition=E2=80=9D).</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Kohlberg moved to dismiss Plaintiffs=E2=80=99 =
claim for specific performance on the basis of the debt-funding condition, =
arguing that Plaintiffs=E2=80=99 claim for specific performance is barred b=
ecause it is undisputed that the full proceeds of the Debt Financing were n=
ot funded. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At trial, Plaintiffs demonstrated that Kohlber=
g=E2=80=99s breach of Section 6.15(a) contributed materially to Kohlberg=E2=
=80=99s failure to obtain Debt Funding. Plaintiffs proved that each of the =
Lenders were willing to execute Debt Financing on the terms of the DCL and =
that Kohlberg refused to move forward. In the words of one of the Lenders, =
when Kohlberg made the Financing Demands, =E2=80=9Cthey changed the ask and=
 risk profile of the deal and were not willing to adjust the economics, so =
they were really looking for a way out.=E2=80=9D The non-occurrence of Debt=
 Financing, therefore, was due materially to Kohlberg=E2=80=99s failure to =
move forward toward a final credit agreement on the terms of the DCL.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The deal <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/28351521.280590/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cua29obGJlcmcuY29tL25ld3M=
va29obGJlcmctY29tcGFueS1hY3F1aXJlcy1kZWNvcGFjLWZyb20tc25vdy1waGlwcHMtZ3JvdX=
AtbGxjLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB57b4b761/email" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">closed in May 202=
1</a>,=C2=A0a few weeks after her decision; I guess Kohlberg figured out it=
s financing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway I know I am late to it but I hope you e=
njoyed this digression into the recent history of Delaware M&amp;A litigati=
on. McCormick was a vice chancellor at the time of this opinion; she is now=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28351521.280590/a=
HR0cHM6Ly9jb3VydHMuZGVsYXdhcmUuZ292L2NoYW5jZXJ5L2p1ZGdlcy5hc3B4/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cBbc72dead/email" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the chancellor</a>,=C2=A0the chief ju=
dge of the Delaware court that hears basically all high-stakes merger litig=
ation in the US. It will be interesting to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/28351521.280590/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMj=
AyMi8wNy8wOC9idXNpbmVzcy9tdXNrLXR3aXR0ZXItZGVhbC5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cBde5cae8a/email" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">see what she does next</a>.</p>
