<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/28351521.280590/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoa=
XZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzAwMDE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTkxMzAwL2QzNzA2NzdkZXg5=
OTIuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1faf6cc7/email" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">a letter from Twi=
tter Inc.=E2=80=99s lawyers</a>=C2=A0to Elon Musk=E2=80=99s lawyers about <=
em>their </em>merger agreement:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s and the other Musk Parties=
=E2=80=99 purported termination is invalid and wrongful, and it constitutes=
 a repudiation of their obligations under the Agreement. Contrary to the as=
sertions in your letter, Twitter has breached none of its obligations under=
 the Agreement, and Twitter has not suffered and is not likely to suffer a =
Company Material Adverse Effect. The purported termination is invalid for t=
he independent reason that Mr. Musk and the other Musk Parties have knowing=
ly, intentionally, willfully, and materially breached the Agreement, includ=
ing but not limited to Sections 6.3, 6.8, and 6.10 thereof. The Agreement i=
s not terminated, the Bank Debt Commitment Letter and the Equity Commitment=
 Letter remain in effect, and Twitter demands that Mr. Musk and the other M=
usk Parties comply with their obligations under the Agreement, including th=
eir obligations to use their respective reasonable best efforts to consumma=
te and make effective the transactions contemplated by the Agreement (inclu=
ding by taking all steps necessary to obtain a favorable outcome under the =
United Kingdom=E2=80=99s National Security and Investment Act 2021), the Ba=
nk Debt Commitment Letter, and the Equity Commitment Letter. As it has done=
, Twitter will continue to provide information reasonably requested by Mr. =
Musk under the Agreement and to diligently take all measures required to cl=
ose the transaction.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twitter reserves all contractual, legal, and o=
ther rights, including its right to specifically enforce the Musk Parties=
=E2=80=99 obligations under the Agreement.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Twitter=E2=80=99s lawyers are Wachtell, Lipton=
, Rosen &amp; Katz; disclosure, I worked there a long time ago. If you=E2=
=80=99re following along at home, when Wachtell says =E2=80=9CMr. Musk =E2=
=80=A6 breached =E2=80=A6 Sections 6.3, 6.8, and 6.10,=E2=80=9D that is a s=
horthand way of saying that Musk has not been using his reasonable best eff=
orts to get the deal closed (<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/28351521.280590/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9k=
YXRhLzE0MTgwOTEvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIyMTc2NzUzL2QyODMxMTlkcHJlcjE0YS5odG0jYW54YXR=
vYzI4MzExOV81OA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa2775784/email" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
